#!/usr/bin/pooscript
# fortune - display a random fortune

fortunes = [
    "The best way to predict the future is to invent it.",
    "In the land of the blind, the one-eyed man is king.",
    "A bug in the code is worth two in the documentation.",
    "Never trust a computer you can't throw out a window. - Steve Wozniak",
    "To err is human, to really foul things up requires a computer.",
    "There are only 10 types of people: those who understand binary and those who don't.",
    "Passwords are like underwear: change them regularly, don't share them, and don't leave them lying around.",
    "The trouble with the world is that the stupid are cocksure and the intelligent full of doubt. - Bertrand Russell",
    "A journey of a thousand miles begins with a single 'sudo'.",
    "Always code as if the person who ends up maintaining your code is a violent psychopath who knows where you live.",
    "It's not a bug, it's an undocumented feature!",
    "Real programmers don't comment their code. If it was hard to write, it should be hard to understand.",
    "In a world without walls, who needs Windows?",
    "I'm not anti-social, I'm just not user-friendly.",
    "Keyboard not found. Press F1 to continue.",
    "404: Fortune not found. Just kidding, here's your fortune!",
    "The problem with troubleshooting is that trouble shoots back.",
    "I would love to change the world, but they won't give me the source code.",
    "Programming is like sex: one mistake and you're supporting it for life.",
    "If at first you don't succeed, call it version 1.0.",
    "Artificial Intelligence is no match for natural stupidity.",
    "My software never has bugs. It just develops random features.",
    "Computers are useless. They can only give you answers. - Pablo Picasso",
    "Java is to JavaScript what Car is to Carpet.",
    "There's no place like 127.0.0.1",
    "sudo make me a sandwich.",
    "The quieter you become, the more you can hear. - Ram Dass",
    "Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic. - Arthur C. Clarke",
    "The Internet? We are not interested in it. - Bill Gates, 1993",
    "You have been terminated. - The future",
]

# Use time() as seed for pseudo-random selection
seed = int(time() * 1000) % len(fortunes)
print(fortunes[seed])
